**APPROVED**

The critical issue from the prior review (Issue 1: monkey-patching `window.showPage`) has been correctly resolved. Here is the verification:

**Fix verification — MutationObserver approach:**

The `app.js` `showPage` function (lines 3-6) does exactly what is required:
```javascript
function showPage(id) {
  document.querySelectorAll(".page").forEach(function (p) {
    p.classList.toggle("active", p.id === "page-" + id);
  });
  ...
}
```

It adds the `active` class to the matching `.page` section. The plan's fix in `performance.js` (lines 1146-1155) correctly observes this:

```javascript
new MutationObserver(function() {
  if (perfPage.classList.contains("active")) init();
}).observe(perfPage, { attributes: true, attributeFilter: ["class"] });
```

This is a clean, correct pattern: the observer watches only the `class` attribute on `#page-performance`, fires when `app.js` toggles `active` onto it, and calls `init()`. The immediate check on DOMContentLoaded also handles the direct-hash case correctly.

**No remaining critical issues found.** All other aspects of the plan are sound — backend routes use proper validation, cache/dedup logic is correct, TDD steps confirm failures before implementation, and the vault helpers are well-structured.
